prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Records more than 25 years old are open for research with select materials restricted as noted. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC.

otherfindaid.head: Other Finding Aids
otherfindaid.p: For additional Medical Letter materials open for research see:
FA241 Rockefeller University collection of the Medical Lettter publication

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Contents includes: original manuscripts, reprints, advertising and package inserts, sources check, consultatnts drafts, manufacturers replies, and bibliography.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Medical Letter on Drugs and Therapeutics is an independent, non-profit publication providing unbiased critical evaluation of drugs in terms of their effectiveness, adverse effects and possible alternative medications.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Use agreement is required prior to providing access. See RAC Head of Reference for assistance.
